AN ACT making appropriations to the Office of the Secretary of
State for the replacement of certain equipment and certain
costs related to elections; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State General
2 Fund to the Office of the Secretary of State the sum of $460,423 for
3 the replacement of computers and information technology
4 equipment.
5 Sec. 2. There is hereby appropriated from the State General
6 Fund to the Office of the Secretary of State the sum of $1,462,864
7 for the costs of voter education materials and outreach, ballot
8 translation and interpretive services and travel.
9 Sec. 3. There is hereby appropriated from the State General
10 Fund to the Office of the Secretary of State the sum of $26,000 for
11 the HAVA Election Reform budget account for costs associated
12 with voter identity verification.
13 Sec. 4. Any remaining balance of an appropriation made by
14 sections 1, 2 and 3 of this act must not be committed for expenditure
